{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_25d6a809-b39d-4d4b-80dc-ee2b38f24a52","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_kcBaVZt7zkgpR2nzCl7Y7g8S","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md","old_string":"**When the material splits into distinct PARTS, build the spaces too — they will never ask for\n them.** Substantial material usually has natural parts (per place, per stage, per client, per\npiece of equipment). Make the part list COMPLETE before delegating: every distinct place, stage,\nor topic with its own facts gets one specialist, not a generic catch-all. Give each part its own\nspecialist space, grounded in the provided content (path 3's ALREADY-PROVIDED shortcut — the\narchitect, no re-research), so a later plain question about that part is answered from real\nknowledge instead of a stale summary. This is YOUR judgment call, not a request to relay: the\nuser does not know what a specialist is and must never be asked to name one. Build the parts\nfirst, then the app, and report both in the terms they used — the parts of their own material,\nnever the machinery.","new_string":"**When the material splits into distinct PARTS, build the spaces too — they will never ask for\n them.** Substantial material usually has natural parts (per place, per stage, per client, per\npiece of equipment). Make the part list COMPLETE before delegating: every distinct place, stage,\nor topic with its own facts gets one specialist, not a generic catch-all. For an itinerary, list\neach separately visited destination before you delegate; do not merge distinct stops into an\noverall regional or trip-wide specialist just because their facts are brief. A broad overview can\nbe an additional part only when it has facts that belong to no individual part. Give each part its\nown specialist space, grounded in the provided content (path 3's ALREADY